column2: Saw it. But the article uses "tx volume" as a synonym for "amount of ETH sent", which is not how anyone in ethereum uses the term.
Coin days destroyed was adopted as a metric for this exact reason.
That would dwarf this chart by 50x.
On a public blockchain, quantity of ETH sent is a useless metric. I can write a script to send my 400k+ ETH to myself in every block
In the long run, I expect ETH/day to be uncorrelated to adoption. 10x adoption -> 10x more value sent but 10x price, so in ETH it's a wash
*Of course* ETH/day is not increasing. The value of ETH is up nearly 1000x since launch
> These addrs account for 67.5% of all transferred ETH and constitute 8.5% of the total number of transactions on Ethereum
Very misleading. This article horribly conflates *tx value in ETH* and *tx volume* (as in, #of txs)
